args:
As Ieyasu and the others begin digging beneath
the well, imperial soldiers attack, drawn there
by talk of buried gold. Marishiten repels them,
and soon after, Ieyasu finds a cave likely carved
out by his ancestor. They decide to call for help.
Now slowly lower the rope.\nYes, just like that.
Hm... There's no water down here.
Here. I brought the shovel and pick.
Surprising no one, even though this was\nall her idea, she's justâ€”
JUST nothing. I'm vigilantly watching over\ncamp. There's no telling when fiends might\nattack. Go on and dig away, worry-free.
She is consistent, if nothing else. Posting\na lookout is sensible, at any rate. Best to\nleave it to her if she's volunteering.
Sure. So, what's our plan?\nJust pick a direction and start digging?
No. If something was hidden here,\nthen covered back up...
...we should look where the soil is looser.\nLike right here, for instance.
I'm glad you're so into this, Ieyasu. That's\nstage one of Project Celestial Rock Cave\ndone and dusted.
Now to prepare for my next move with a\nreinvigorating nap. Zzz...
...That's the sound of the perimeter alarm\nI set up. Someone's coming.
Ugh. It's just dirt, dirt, and more dirt.\nI'm getting bored.
I'm rather enjoying myself. Being able to\ntune out the world and focus on a physical\ntask like thisâ€”hm?
My shovel struck something solid.\nHave we hit bedrock? Or...
Ah! Look what I've turned up, Marishiten.
What is it? It's rusted bright red, but it's...\nsome sort of tool? It has a handle.
Seems like exactly the sort of thing a\nfellow might want if he were burying\nsomething. Heh heh.
You seem awfully happy for a guy who\njust found some junk in the ground.
Even I'm surprised at how excited I feel\nto see something resembling proof of our\nhypothesis. Come, let's keep digging.

(Get a load of him, getting all worked up
over a scrap of rusted metal on a stick.
Not something you usually see from
Mister Serious.)
Ahoy down there! You two got a minute?
ï¼‚The samurai clad in eyes of eight...\nHe dug the well, it couldn't wait...ï¼‚
Too caught up playing in the dirt to hear,\nhuh? Well, whatever.
Knee-deep in dirt and weirdly glad about\nit. Why, am I not enough?
Oh, I suspect you're plenty. Someone's\ncoming this way. Thought I'd give you\na little warning, that's all.
What are you people doing here?
Enjoying a nice, relaxing day.\nWhy, what's YOUR story?
We've come on reports of buried treasure.\nWe'll be investigating the area.
The higher-ups must be awfully bored,\nsending us out here chasing after idiotic\nfolk legends.
Raising fiends costs money. I think they're\nfollowing any leads they can. You're not\nwrong that the mission's idiotic, though.
Enough blithering! Idiotic or not,\nyou'll shut up and do your jobs!
(These guys are imperial soldiers, yeah?\nDo we tell them about the well?)
(Uh, no? The less we contribute to the\nEmpire's war chest, the happier we'll all\nbe.)
I feel for you, gentlemen, I really do.\nThere's a fat lotta nothing here, though.\nWhy not just call it a day?
See? This lady gets it. We can just write\non the report that we looked but didn't find\nany sign ofâ€”
You two have got to get down here!\nI've found something incredible.
Where did that voice come from?
Whoaaa, check it out! There's a well!\nYou don't think that's the, uh...whatsit?
The well from the legend?! Whoa! That\nwhole story about the buried treasure's\nstarting to feel a little more real, huh?
And yet you said only an idiot would\nbelieve a tale like that mere minutes ago.
Hold on. The two of you are starting to look\nawfully suspicious. What are you REALLY\ndoing here?
What if I said ï¼‚the same thing you guys\nare doingï¼‚?
Then you would be confessing to the crime\nof conspiracy to steal the (provisional) war\nfunds of the Empire.
Yeah! So if you don't want to have a real\nbad day, clear out!
Don't threaten a lady with a good time.\nMitsuhide, tell Ieyasu to stay down there\na minute.
You see, we're not too keen on backing\ndown, either. So if you're looking to do this\nthe hard way, Marishiten is your dragon!
I shall be curious to see how long that\nconfidence holds. Let's go, boys! Hraaaah!
Are you guys for real? That was laughable.
Shut up! We'll be back, so just you wait.\n...MEN! We're leaving.
Goodness, sirs. You look like you've been\nthrough the wringer. Come and rest up in\nour village!
Who the hell are all YOU people?!
You'll find no better respite than at our inn!\nI'll even go all-out on dinner, just for you!
We've got healing ointments for sale!\nGuests at the inn get 20 percent off!
Hey, whoa, hands off the goods, lady!\nGAH! What kinda gorilla grip...?!
All right, everyone! Let's escort these\nhonored guests back to the village!
Hey! Let go ofâ€”LET ME GOOOOO!
That was the Aquagi crowd, right?\nWhere'd THEY all pop out of?
Who knows? But that's sure some\nenthusiastic hospitality.
I repeat: their idea of ï¼‚hospitalityï¼‚ is only\nslightly terrifying. Hm...? Wait a minute.
If we knew that, we'd be there with spades\nin hand right now! Ho ho ho.
(If they came here, doesn't that mean they\nknow about the well? And by that logicâ€”)
Poor Ieyasu must be tired of waiting by\nnow. I'll keep watch. You go.
Hey, Ieyasu. Just finished with that little\nerrand up topside. What'd you want to\nshow us?
What is this? Some kind of cavern? The\nslope heads down further underground.
I found the entrance while I was digging.\nIf I may direct your attention to the wall...
Hm? It's caked in mud, but it's inlaid\nwith stones, stacked one upon the next.
Supports, to keep the tunnel from\ncollapsing, I suspect. And I found\nthis further in.
A pill box with an eight boar's eye design.\nMy family's emblem... And it's quite old.
If there's something here with your family\ncrest on it, this cave must have beenâ€”
Dug out by the tanuki?\nIt's looking more and more likely, yes.
But it seems there was a cave-in deeper\ninside. It's blocked tight with soil and rock.\nI don't think we'll get through by ourselves.
You gonna hang up your proverbial hat,\nthen?
Giving up now would make for quite\nthe anticlimax. I'd like to call in some\nbackup instead.
